## Section 2: System Architecture Overview

The system has four sequential layers. Each layer's output feeds the next, and every handoff is visible and auditable.

```
Raw Documents + External Sources + Primary Notes
                      ↓
         LAYER 1 — DATA INGESTOR
    (Parse, extract, clean, structure)
                      ↓
      LAYER 2 — ML INTELLIGENCE LAYER
  (FinBERT + Isolation Forest + Graph Engine)
                      ↓
       LAYER 3 — FIVE CS SCORECARD
     (Aggregate signals → scores → decision)
                      ↓
        LAYER 4 — LLM SYNTHESIS
      (CAM narrative + recommendation)
                      ↓
         Interactive UI + Word/PDF CAM
```

Every layer's output is stored, labeled, and linked forward and backward. A judge can start at the final CAM recommendation and drill all the way back to the exact sentence in a PDF that triggered a risk signal. That is the explainability promise.

